# Debenture Bridge
## Problem Description
In Indian market there are large number of unbanked people. 
It's a sad state and when we know that there are people who will be able to help them at a much better level there is no Bridge that gaps between the borrows and the lenders and nobody feels that they are going to be cheated.
![alt text](https://arizent.brightspotcdn.com/ba/b9/f6a0e14643a9aab2e87d8df769a5/ab-032117-kamat.jpeg)
Here are some stats from 2015. 
## Our Solution
We at debenture Bridge target unavailability of micro loans for poor and unbanked people. 
There are no long documents required skepticism is eradicated at its best which is among the lenders. 
Introducing blockchain in our application we try to provide immutable records. 

For the unbanked the guaranteer will be the panchayat of the village from which he is belonging. 

Further, let's dive more into it and understand the work-flow!

![alt text](data:image/png;base64,)

## Novelty
1-Integration of a trustworthy organisation as a verifier removes skepticism among lenders.

2-Implementation of blockchain ensures immutibility of records.

3-No conventional paperwork required.

4-No high charging collateral required.




## FAQ

#### Question 1

What is the role of panchayat, why it will help, and how it will enable trust?

Answer 1

Panchayat will act as a guarunteer of the borrower here and stands questionable if borrower fails to pay back the money.
It will be interested in helping us as we will give 1% of the interest charged.
The trust on panchayat will be firm because as for borrower it is the most reachable law and order maintaing organisation and same stands for the lender asit is government run body.

#### Question 2
What is the business plan?
Answer 2
An interest amount of 10% willl be charged from the borrower from which the lender will be holding 8% and the other 2% will be divided between the panchayat and debenture bridge equally.
